    <item>
      <title>12.10 Ujun</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-10-ujun/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-10-ujun/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 08 Nov 2023 08:55:30 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;12.10 Ujun&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N:  A name for a character we&amp;#8217;ve met around the time of the hanged paper doll case, 199 chapters ago&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;卯純, otherwise known as Maochun in Chinese. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-09-the-injured-and-the-chaperone/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Former Consort Lishu’s older brother was called Ujun.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao had seen him before. He was the one Basen had beaten up along with Lishu’s father, Uryuu.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I have a feeling that his teeth were a little crooked last time.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Of course, Maomao’s brain doesn’t remember anything aside from medicine, so she had long forgotten his face already.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I guess I should probably be calling him Lishu’s older brother.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But with this, wouldn’t that make her mix him up with Rahan’s older brother? But it took time for Maomao to remember the names of strangers. That being said, she didn’t feel like remembering his name.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;But what if I overlap him with Rahan’s older brother?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;At the end of her thoughts, to respect Rahan’s older brother, she stored Ujun’s name in her brain. Note that she has already forgotten the rude patient’s name.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After the patient was treated, Ujun left.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It became a troublesome matter,” Court Physician Ri said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How is it troublesome?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Court Physician Ri scratched his head. “Remember how I said that the spats have been intense lately? I was told to hear both sides of the story, even if they were from sparring.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We’ve only heard one side of the story today, I see. Shouldn’t it be fine?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If Former Consort Lishu was the source of the argument, she could see why Basen got involved. If Maomao’s gut feeling was correct, Basen seems to have some reservations towards Lishu.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I understand Basen-sama quite a bit. Do you think he could turn a blind eye to a woman, let alone a former consort, getting mocked?” Maomao said something plausible.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Lishu was already a former high ranking consort. The moment she left the inner palace, she was no longer a flower of the inner palace. She must be feeling more at ease with this, when compared with the idea of sleeping with his imperial majesty who was a fatherly figure to her. But this was a matter assuming there were no prying eyes…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We still have to get our records straight, but Basen-sama, huh. There’s no way we can have him directly come to us, huh.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao suddenly had a thought. Basen in her impressions wasn’t particularly scary. He was the son of Gaoshun, a diligent attendant who liked cute things, whom he was no match for. Also, he was no match for his mother, nor his sister, and was always teased by his sister-in-law. He was a reckless bear clad in human skin; if you don’t harm him, he won’t attack you.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Why is he so on guard?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;So Maomao thought, but considering the most common conception of him, Basen was an elite who directly served the imperial brother.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Do you think the likes of me can go up and talk to him directly?” Court Physician Ri said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Come to think of it, Court Physician Ri didn’t really have any contact with Basen.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In the western capital, Court Physician Ri was in the town’s medical office. Basen had visited the place, but he was there as Jinshi’s representative in the form of a consolation visit. He was acting as an imperial so the court physician might want to keep his distance.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;That time he might have seemed more intimidating than usual.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I don’t think he’s someone who’d mind that much. If you tell him that it’s part of work, he won’t wrench your arm off,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If we’re talking about someone who’d get wrenched off, it’d be Tianyu.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hahaha, he might actually get his head wrenched off.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Court Physician Ri does make funny jokes every now and then&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought. Note that his eyes were not laughing.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But that patient before was treating Basen-sama quite rudely,” she said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, that person is also from a named clan. He wasn&amp;#8217;t bestowed with the clan name,&amp;nbsp; however.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I see.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;That was why he was haughty towards Ujun and Basen, both of whom were also from named clans. He seemed to be from a collateral line–no need to ask which clan he was from.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But Court Physician Ri, you were treating those two like you were their superior.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Family background aside, in terms of position I am higher than those two. Court Physician Liu has taught me to not ever be put down by patients in the medical office.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Quite so&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao also understood. It would be troubling if they couldn’t provide the appropriate treatment due to a layman untactfully butting in.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“However, that behaviour was truly unacceptable. The U clan has been in decline eversince Lishu-sama left the inner palace. But to even go against Basen-sama…” Court Physician Ri sighed as he cleared away the tools. “The Ma clan are guards who work directly for the imperial family. Thus, they always accompany their master without holding a position. And yet an idiot who misunderstood assumed his lack of position equated to incompetence and picked a fight with him.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hahahaha, he was lucky that he didn’t get his organs ruptured.” Maomao packed the rest of the bandages onto the shelf.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, Court Physician Ri was being quite talkative today.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Um, Court Physician Ri.” Maomao watched Court Physician Ri as he lightly placed down the report. He sidled over to her. “Could it be that you are against going to Basen-sama to ask for details?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“N-not at all…” Court Physician Ri’s eyes wandered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Could it be that it’s a hassle to go to where Basen-sama is?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“If you tell me it’s work, I’d go, but…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It didn’t seem like he was keen about it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A lightbulb flashed in Maomao’s mind. “If Court Physician Ri gives me the order, I can go on your behalf. How about that?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Oh, will you?” He sounded like he’d been waiting for her to say so.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It’d be more patronising if it were someone else saying this, but it was Court Physician Ri. He was always looking out for her, so it can’t be helped.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Certainly.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Occasionally, Maomao will earnestly do as she was told.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N: If Lishu was still Riishu, Ujun would&amp;#8217;ve been another ROB, and then the original ROB would have been robbed of his nickname, when he already has his real name struggles to deal with. Poor dude. But a LOB and a ROB would&amp;#8217;ve been funny.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-11-the-two-are-chummy/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-10-ujun/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-4151-670843c56807a' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20241010#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=4151&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-4151-670843c56807a' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-4151-670843c56807a' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-10-ujun/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
