    <item>
      <title>11.09 Love</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-09-love/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-09-love/</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 17 Oct 2023 08:35:48 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;11.09 Love&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-08-court-physician-assistants-on-holiday/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As far as En’en was aware, Rakan’s residence had normal servants, as well as servants who were not.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Normal servants were primarily people that Rahan, the head of the household’s adoptive son, had brought in.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Servants who were not were people that Rakan himself had taken in from who-knows-where.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The man known as Tactician Rakan was utterly unremarkable in terms of appearances alone–medium build, foxy eyes, a nasty mouth. If there was anything about him that stood out, would it be that he wears a foreign monocle? He was technically a military officer, but he could barely lift a thing. No stamina to speak of either, and was terrible with moving vehicles to boot. The only thing he was capable of was horse riding, as it was said that he could ride like most people, like he did when he stayed at Isei Province in the past.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Truth be told, he was a useless person who only got a good position thanks to his family background. That was the evaluation of Rakan from a few decades ago.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was his return following the insurrection that broke out at the western capital when his evaluation changed completely.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Alone, he was a hopeless dullard, but when it came to using others, he alone was better than anyone else.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A servant brought in by such a man would have to be anything but ordinary.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Sanfan, dressed in male garb, was preparing tea. She was one of the servants that Rakan had brought in.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She was short for a man, but tall for a woman–roughly the same height as Yao. En’en confirmed that she was female. A servant that showed up at Rakan’s place around five years ago.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-sama, En’en-san. Pardon me for calling you.” Sanfan had a faint smile on her handsome face.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How can I help you?” Instead of Enen, Maomao replied. She looked so annoyed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I thought to entertain our guest—”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Enough with the pleasantries. Can we move on to the main topic?&amp;#8221; En&amp;#8217;en cut in.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As if Maomao was going to say the same thing, she was nodding. She shrewdly helped herself to the tea and crackers.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;I guess you&amp;#8217;re right. Allow me to get to the point. This is about your Yao-san.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Yao-san? That&amp;#8217;s quite an overfamiliar way you&amp;#8217;re calling her.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;From how En&amp;#8217;en saw it, Sanfan had no right to call Yao in such a way.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Isn&amp;#8217;t she Vice Minister Lu&amp;#8217;s niece? From my investigations, I am aware that she hates her uncle&amp;#8217;s influence. Doesn&amp;#8217;t she just look like a mere court lady? Is she so noble that you need to attach honorifics to her name?” Sanfan&amp;#8217;s expression didn&amp;#8217;t change. She had no more than a faint smile, but her eyes were laughing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Like how En&amp;#8217;en investigated Sanfan&amp;#8217;s background, Sanfan had investigated En&amp;#8217;en and Yao&amp;#8217;s backgrounds in kind. It seems she also investigated Maomao&amp;#8217;s, as the snacks laid out were crisp salty crackers just the way she liked it. Once again, Maomao was crunching away.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;With that being said, I&amp;#8217;m not here to pick a fight with you. I have called for you two, wishing you to speak about a matter that would be beneficial to both sides.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Beneficial to both sides?&amp;#8221; Maomao eyed her suspiciously.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;What kind of benefits?&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Yes. So I believe that there are no gains for anyone even if Yao-san stays at this residence for any longer. I have found the perfect new property I would like to recommend to you.&amp;#8221; She laid out a house plan that had been drawn on a sheet of paper. It was larger than the room En&amp;#8217;en and Yao were in; the kitchen had a lot of stoves and it was close to the well. “It’s in a safe area that’s close to a market. It’s also close to your workplace. And the rent is only this much!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The number of fingers she held out was certainly exceptional. Instead of En’en, Maomao’s eyes shone and she made grabby hands. “With these dimensions, medicinal herb, processing…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Certainly, their workplace dorm wasn’t suitable for medicinal herb processing.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It is quite a good place,” En’en said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Isn’t that right? Then, shall you move at once?” Sanfan asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, is what I would like to immediately say, but I would like to confirm some things. What is wrong with us staying at this residence?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Quite the distrustful personality, huh. I just want to say that it’s indecent to have a young lady of a good family freeloading at a gentleman’s house.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That is true. If you think about it normally, I’d see it as a suggestion that thinks about Yao-sama.” En’en stared at Sanfan.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“En’en,” Maomao poked her, whispering, brows furrowed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What’s wrong, Maomao?” En’en whispered back.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How about taking up her offer at once? It’s a good place. I don’t think she’s trying to swindle you. Is there something that you’re displeased with?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Don’t you feel that Sanfan-san is looking down on milady?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Isn’t it just you?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, I don’t think so.” En’en tersely looked at Sanfan. “Sanfan-san’s words are reasonable, but I wonder if you are really thinking about Yao-sama?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, I’m thinking about Rahan-sama,” Sanfan replied with a radiant smile.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en thought thus:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Sanfan’s proposal certainly wasn’t bad. However, it doesn’t place respect towards Yao. Why was that?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Honestly, I wonder what to think about a girl of marriageable age coming to live in a gentleman’s house because she finds her uncle talking about marriage to her an annoyance. And more importantly, the annoying uncle is currently far away in the western lands with no knowing of when he returns. Nonetheless, her nerve to continue staying here is something I don’t understand.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en was distressed by Sanfan’s statement. Maomao poked her elbow again.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“En’en, could it be that you’re in support of the offer, but since you can’t stand Sanfan-san, you honestly don’t want to voice your approval?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;no, not at all.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Your face is currently really strained.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then hurry up and accept it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Mmmm, I’ll need to discuss this sort of thing with milady.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“En’en doesn’t win against Yao-san, I see.” Maomao looked exasperated.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are you two done with your secret discussion?” Sanfan asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I cannot say anything about moving until after I discuss with milady,” En’en declared.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that so? Not even when I give you your ideal house that you have been speaking to the other servants about?” Sanfan tilted her head.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en got irritated that she kept humouring the other party. “Then, let’s ask you from the opposite direction. Why is Sanfan-san eager to chase us, milady especially, out? I would like to ask you in detail.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en kind of wanted to have Sanfan to act a little suspiciously. However, Sanfan replied clearly without a change in expression:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I love Rahan-sama. I will do anything for him. So, if a naive chit of a girl comes in with some misunderstanding, acting like she’s forcing herself onto him, what am I to say about reflexively getting in her way?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Who the hell are you to call her a naive chit—”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en was about pitch forward, when—&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Pwah!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao was the one who spat out glittering droplets that scattered in the air. It was extremely filthy; En’en unintentionally took half a step back.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’m sorry,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No…” Sanfan’s face was covered in the spat out tea and cracker crumbs.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But have you regained your sanity?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What do you mean by sanity?” Sanfan wiped her face with a towel.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“We’re talking about that bushy glasses guy here. You know? That average-faced short guy who’s always thinking about ways to make money, who places importance on no future troubles with his female relationships, who’d even wonder if he could produce a child with a man if their numbers are beautiful?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I am aware. Furthermore, he cuts people off completely, and forces people he can’t get along with into a predicament, without dirtying his own hands or leaving behind any evidence of the deed. His coordination is catastrophic, he can’t ride a horse, and nor can he pull the string of a bow. The definition of an egghead.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No matter how you see it, isn’t he a good for nothing man?” Maomao looked dumbfounded. Her reaction was huge, so En’en’s anger over Yao getting called a chit abated a little.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But in response, there was a slight blush to Sanfan’s cheeks. “Well, his looks aren’t much to speak of, but he’s the one who gave me the opportunity to live as I want. If it’s for the sake of beautiful things, I won’t twist my way of thinking.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en felt bad that the other woman was making the face of a love-struck maiden, but she really couldn’t see Rahan like that. “Whatever Sanfan-san believes, I reckon a gentleman like that will go on to marry a girl from a respectable family once he’s tired of playing around. He’ll pretend his dalliances never happened and act like he’s made a good family. Would you still be okay with that? With your current position, I don’t think you have what it takes to become the madam of this household.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En’en’s evaluation of Rahan was harsh, but she didn’t think she was entirely wrong. She didn’t know Sanfan’s former family’s pedigree, but she was currently a mere servant.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I know that very well. Which is why, even though I am Sanfan, I don’t have problems with being Erfan either. That’s why I hope the future madam of this residence is a personage I wish to support.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;“&amp;#8230;”” En’en inadvertently exchanged looks with Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Sanfan was more fanatical than they thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, let’s stop! There are plenty of gentlemen in this world that are heaps better than Rahan!” Maomao cried.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao-sama. You won’t be able to find a gentleman who can think in the way Rahan-sama does, you know?” Sanfan replied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sanfan-san, even if you’re no match for milady, you’re quite attractive. You are only currently affected by tunnel vision,” En’en said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Small-minded gentlemen who pick a woman based on their looks have never interested me in the first place.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, that guy definitely goes for appearances. He loves beauties depending on their numbers! Face reality, please!” Maomao shook Sanfan by her shoulders.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even En’en kind of understood Maomao’s feelings. She couldn’t understand how a bespectacled man like that was popular. Was Rahan born under that sort of star?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;However, at the same time, she considered if she should persuade Yao to quickly move to the new property that Sanfan recommended. She didn’t have the confidence that she could explain it well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Above all, she had a certain sense of unease.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If, hypothetically, by some chance, by some minuscule chance, the impossible…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Of which Yao, just like Sanfan, was in love with Rahan, what would she do?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;En&amp;#8217;en felt it was impossible, probably the rashness of youth, but despite that, she wanted to ascertain it by urging her to move. She was in the most difficult spot.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-10-the-night-visit/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-09-love/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-4073-670843c5ae1d4' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20241010#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=4073&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-4073-670843c5ae1d4' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-4073-670843c5ae1d4' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/11-09-love/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
