    <item>
      <title>12.06 Joka&amp;#8217;s Request</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-06-jokas-request/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-06-jokas-request/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 07 Oct 2023 10:59:06 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;12.06 Joka&amp;#8217;s Request&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-05-the-village-settlement/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After she finished eating her street stall bought grilled skewers, Maomao pouted.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao, Sazen and Yo were inside the cramped pharmacy of Rokushoukan. As for what they were doing, they were checking inventory and the account book.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Hey, aren’t they charging exorbitant prices for medicinal herbs lately?&amp;#8221; Maomao, squinting, checked the purchasing price.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Right? It&amp;#8217;s high, right? But Kokuyou told me they won’t sell it to us if not at this price,&amp;#8221; Sazen grumbled. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Speaking of the all-important Kokuyou, with how cramped the pharmacy was, he was outside playing with the children alongside Chue. Chou&amp;#8217;u was also playing with them. The boy&amp;#8217;s eyes met with Maomao’s,&amp;nbsp; but seeing how he ignored her, he must be at a sensitive age.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Ahh, this is expensive too. They took advantage of us by claiming how it could only be grown on wet soil.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There were limits to cultivating medicinal herbs on a field. With limited procurement channels, they must not ever deal with a high hand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“One of these days, you’ll be told to buy wholesale, so it’s better if you remember the cost of herbal medicines,&amp;#8221; Maomao said, showing Yo, who looked idle, the account book. Normally it wasn’t something to carelessly show people, but she doubted the girl would abuse it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She continued, “Basically, you’ll be accompanied by another court physician to buy wholesale, but bad vendors will aim for the moment you are alone to come sell you their wares. They would say things like: &amp;#8216;This is all that is left&amp;#8217;, &amp;#8216;I don’t know when I can get this back in stock again,&amp;#8217; so take note. You could also be made to buy inferior goods.’&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Understood,” Yo answered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I’ve been duped many times too,” Sazen sighed deeply.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sazen is bad at business,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Shut it. I’m a former farmer, oi.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Former farmer.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On that note, how was the active farmer–Rahan’s older brother–faring? She was planning to approach him on getting him to work on cultivating herbal medicines aside from potato and wheat when he returned.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After they were done reviewing the account book, they looked into the inventory. At the same time, she checked the medicine Sazen compounded.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“H-how is it?” Sazen peeked at Maomao’s expression.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Not bad. Not great either. Pass.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Whaat? I made it according to how I was taught.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You have to consider not just what you were taught, but also what ways you can make it easier to take.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Sazen pouted while taking out a notebook. There were compounding methods and whatnot written in it. Although Sazen wasn’t particularly smart, his diligence was a virtue.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Let’s compound while we’re at it.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yo-san. Can you make a medicine you know of with the ingredients here?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Just an antipyretic and an ointment for cuts,” Yo answered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, try making them.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In the meantime, Maomao continued checking their stock.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yo’s movements were clumsy, but her methodology was correct.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Did Kokuyou teach you?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, Kokuyou-san taught the village kids how to read and how to make medicine. Being a village settlement, people were always getting hurt.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao thought Yo was taciturn, but the girl turned out to be surprisingly talkative.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Aside from Yo-san’s family, did Kokuyou not give others the smallpox treatment?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.my dad was the only one who knew of the terrors of smallpox. The other villagers didn’t ask. In particular, the village headman was also the witch doctor, so Kokuyou was a nuisance.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What bad luck he has, Kokuyou.” Sazen added to the conversation as he checked the account book. “No matter how you see it, that guy did nothing wrong, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I have no idea why you hit him&lt;/em&gt;, Sazen’s eyes said. Yo awkwardly lowered her face and grinded medicinal herbs with a pestle.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was the moment Maomao got up, wondering what she should do.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Maomao, you there?&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She heard a listless voice. It was Joka-neechan.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;What is it, Joka-neechan?&amp;#8221; Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Just something I want to ask you. Can you come to my room?&amp;#8221; Joka said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao wondered if she could leave Yo and Sazen alone in the room, but both of them were focused on work. She figured it should be fine for her to temporarily excuse herself.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&amp;#8220;Okay.&amp;#8221; Maomao headed to Joka&amp;#8217;s room&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The characteristic smell of books permeated the room of many bookshelves. Rather than the room of a courtesan, it was more fitting to call it the room of a scholar. In the corner of a bookshelf was the book Maomao brought back from the western capital as a souvenir.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What do you want me to do?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Joka took out a wooden box from a drawer. Inside, laid a green rectangular-shaped slab. “Do you know of this?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Isn’t this the plaque you mentioned that is a clue or something to Joka-neechan’s father?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was a jade plaque. The surface had been shaved off and it was broken in half.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Joka-neechan was born in a brothel. A courtesan gave birth to her and the seed was from some patron. And it was that patron who left her a piece of this plaque.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Joka’s name was imprudent. Normally, the character “Ka” was reserved only for the imperial family. However, Joka’s father was actually a highborn, and the proof laid within the plaque. And so, she used the Ka character–that was Joka’s background story.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As for Joka herself, she didn’t believe she was an imperial; just that a stupid woman got deceived by a man and was given a stolen item or something.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;That being said, to bring in customers, it wasn’t bad to be clad in a slightly mystical air. For the sake of her profession, Joka made use of the story where she might be an illegitimate child of royalty.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I was thinking of asking you to investigate this plaque,” Joka said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You ask me to investigate, but its surface has been shaved off. And isn’t it broken? And above all, didn’t you tell me that you didn’t care who your father was?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“About that. It seems like I’m wrapped up in some slightly troublesome matter.” Joka ran her fingers up her lustrous hair.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Troublesome matter?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yeah. There was a customer who wanted to see the plaque when they heard rumours about me. Of all things, he told me to hand it over to him.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You declined, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I did. I&amp;#8217;ve yet have a use for this plaque while I’m still working. Afterwards, it seems the man who asked for it died. It must be after that. Burglars have broken into Rokushoukan several times to ransack my room. Wouldn’t you find that strange?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao crossed her arm. “Hey, that man, was he young? How did he die?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“He was young. A military officer who was named Fang. Apparently he was caught three-timing and got killed by the women who resented him.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;” Maomao heard a story she had a really good idea about.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;It has to be that guy, right?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The man who hung in the weirdo tactician’s office.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I don’t know how he died, just that it was creepy. Maomao has a lot of acquaintances in court, so I thought you could investigate for me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Got it. Can I have a closer look at the item?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sure.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao checked the jade plaque. The surface was scraped off and it was broken, but she could tell it was once cut from a large piece of jade.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She had no idea if they were royalty or whatever, but being able to arrange for jade like this, would mean they were immensely wealthy.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Hmmm.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao, you can take it with you.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Huh?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Some thief breaking in and stealing it away if I were to leave it with me would be like getting our priorities backwards, right? You can just give it back if you have completely out of ideas about it.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao wondered what she should do as she felt the surface of the plaque.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Mn?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She felt something. When she looked at the side, she discovered a design that hadn’t been shaved off.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Got it. I’ll borrow it for a month. If I don’t know anything by then, I&amp;#8217;ll give it back to you,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sure. I’ll leave it to you,” Joka replied.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao accepted the plaque, wrapped it in a towel and put it in her bosom pocket.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N: Although this is its first appearance in the WN, this plaque already came up in LN13. Also, Maomao was there in person to investigate the robbery attempt in LN14 instead of hearing it as an offhand remark.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-07-the-jade-plaque/"&gt;Next chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-06-jokas-request/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-4035-670843c5c7b72' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20241010#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=4035&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-4035-670843c5c7b72' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-4035-670843c5c7b72' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-06-jokas-request/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
