    <item>
      <title>12.17 The Shin&amp;#8217;s Heirloom (2)</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-17-the-shins-heirloom-2/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-17-the-shins-heirloom-2/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 29 Nov 2023 06:22:48 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;12.17 The Shin&amp;#8217;s Heirloom&amp;nbsp;(2)&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-16-the-shins-heirloom-1/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao sighed deeply. “Then I shall take you up on your offer. I have a few questions.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Speaking of the points that bothered her in the story just now…&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Please tell me the detailed description of the dragon statuette.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The description? The size of it is… it’ll be faster to draw it out,” the matriarch said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The advisor passed writing implements and paper to the matriarch. The matriarch drew out a magnificent dragon.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You’re good at drawing.” Maomao was honestly amazed.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“An amateur’s study.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The dragon she had drawn was a typical dragon Maomao had imagined. It had a long tubular body like a great serpent and a pair of horns. Its foreleg was bearing an orb under its talons, and it had a mane. It was drawn to full scale, so the dragon was enshrined on a pedestal about three &lt;em&gt;sun &lt;/em&gt;in length.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She didn&amp;#8217;t see anything particularly odd about it, aside from this one part. And if Maomao could see it, there was no way Rahan with his keen eyes wouldn’t see it either.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It has four claws?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As Rahan said, the dragon bearing the orb was drawn to have four digits.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, that’s right. Normally it wouldn’t be allowed for non-imperials. However, the emperor at the time loved the crown prince to such an extent. It was proof that even if he had fallen to the level of a subject, he was no doubt his son. The orb, too, was purple,” the matriarch answered.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Purple was the second noblest colour after yellow.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The most exalted of colours was a shade of yellow-red known as ochre &lt;sub&gt;(#FC7F31)&lt;/sub&gt;, a colour only allowed to be worn by the emperor.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is the statuette made from pure gold?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, it wasn’t. I believe it was mixed with silver.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Gold is soft. It was easy to process, but at the time, it was easy to destroy. Adding silver to increase its strength wasn’t anything odd to hear.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao closed her eyes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;An alloy, a mixture with different metals, could have a lowered melting point. But I don’t think gold and silver would be lowered by that much.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If there were no lies in the matriarch’s words, she believed that the heirloom would have been burnt down completely.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Next, can you tell me the specifics of what happened during the fire?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Argh, no more of this! Grandmother, you don’t have to explain. It’s faster If we settle our accounts with the U clan. Let’s go!”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The advisor dropped a fist right onto the grandson’s head. The youngster had been tugging his grandmother’s hand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wooow, I feel like I’ve seen this scene before.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Do all the athletic families speak with body language?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What was the cause of the fire?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;A lamp in the archives had burst into flames,” the matriarch said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that&amp;#8230;SO!” Maomao covered her side in a fluster. The weirdo tactician had suddenly poked her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was an odd gleam to the monocled weirdo’s eyes. His expression was of a dog that had retrieved an item and was expecting praise.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Don’t tell me, he’s trying to tell me that the matriarch lied just now?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The weirdo tactician’s thin eyes became even thinner.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She was thankful that he informed her of the lies, but poking her with a finger was gross, so she slapped his hand away.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;What could her lying about the source of the fire mean?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao kept that in mind and moved on to the next question. “You told me the treasury wasn’t completely burnt down. Specifically, how much had been burnt down?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The matriarch cast her eyes down to retrace her memories. “The treasury didn’t collapse upon itself. However, there were a lot of books that had been burnt to a crisp, so there wasn’t much left.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So you say the books are no good. Then that would mean that furniture would also be no good, right? If you had vases, those should be fine. No, if they were art pieces, then they would have lost their value. Were there any swords or armour?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“There were several swords and armour as art pieces. Also, I remember that generations of trousseau weren’t burnt completely since they were far from the source of the fire.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;At that, the weirdo tactician made no reaction.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then lastly. You said that the U clan put out the fire, but was his visit a planned one? Or did he happen to pass by out of coincidence?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The U clan had planned to visit my family.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, did you know about his visit?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;” At Maomao’s question, the matriarch froze. “&amp;#8230;No, it was a sudden visit.” As if she believed there was no point to lie about this incident, the elderly woman replied honestly.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Why did he suddenly visit?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“&amp;#8230;It was under the Empress Regnant’s orders. As I told you earlier, the U clan followed the Empress Regnant. At the time, my husband had only recently taken over the Shin clan as its head, so he was still young and hot-blooded. He had prattled on to other members of the anti Empress Regnant faction about treating a non-imperial as an imperial. With that in mind, the U clan’s visit would be easily understandable, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“He came to seize the proof of rebellion?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Most probably.” She spoke ambiguously because nothing happened in the end due to the fire. “A large number of our heirlooms became charcoal, but I believe it was a good thing. When you consider the influence of the Empress Regnant at the time, our clan could have perished at the way we were going then. However, the unfortunate thing was that my husband never got to make up with his best friend.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tears rolled down the matriarch’s cheeks. She dabbed her eyes with a towel as if to suppress it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that all of the questions?” The grandson was barely able to speak politely to Maomao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Did you discover anything from that?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What?!” Not just the grandson, the matriarch and the advisor also widened their eyes. “Are you saying you discovered it from the questions just now?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Not everything. But I’ve found a number of points that I’m sceptical about.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Rahan nodded, as if he noticed the details too. The weirdo tactician was studying the matriarch to see if she was lying or not.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What are the sceptical points?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You said that the books were burnt, and the swords, armours and trousseau were partially burnt. There would be bronze mirrors included in the trousseau, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then it &lt;em&gt;is &lt;/em&gt;strange.”&lt;br&gt;“It’s strange.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao and Rahan exchanged glances.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What’s strange about it?” Unusually, the advisor opened his mouth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“So you see….” Rahan started to speak, so Maomao decided to let him do the explaining. “Just now, you mentioned that the golden heirloom statuette had been melted down to nothing. But I find it hard to believe that the fire had burnt hot enough to melt the metal.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Wh-what do you mean?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Bronze mirrors are made of bronze. Bronze and gold have the same melting point.” Rahan’s glasses flashed. “If the bronze mirrors didn’t melt, there is a high chance that the gold didn’t melt either. More importantly, even if the gold did melt, it wouldn’t just disappear. There should be a clump of melted metal somewhere. Gold, in its unprocessed form, is highly valuable. I find it hard to believe you wouldn’t make use of a clump of melted metal.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Is that so?” The matriarch’s eyes rounded in wonder. Normally, a woman from a good family wouldn’t know anything about the temperature to melt metal. It wasn’t common knowledge. In Maomao and Rahan’s case, they had acquired the knowledge from her dad or business relations respectively, so they were special cases.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Th-then, where on earth could the heirloom be?” the grandson asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Before that, I would have to confirm two more things,” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“What is it?” the matriarch asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The U clan visited the Shin clan residence all of a sudden. It was right when there was a fire, and he put it out for you. Is that right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“After he put out the fire, he scrupulously checked the interior of the burnt treasury, to look for proof of rebellion, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Most probably.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;If there was no proof, the Empress Regnant would not be able to do anything to the Shin clan, she thought.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Then, was there really no proof of rebellion?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao reached into her lapels to take out a hair stick of unique tastes. She plucked off one of the amethyst skulls.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Sis, I don’t know what to think about destroying a gift right in front of the person who gave it to you,” Rahan said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao dear, so you only wanted the skulls? Then next time, I’ll make you a rosary of crystal skulls,” Rakan said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;““Please don’t.”” Maomao and Rahan’s voices overlapped.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao showed the matriarch the skull. “The orb the dragon was clutching, would be an amethyst like this, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. The colour is also the same, I think,” the matriarch said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“In that case.” Maomao looked at the brazier in the corner of the room. It was too hot to use a brazier in this season, but it was needed to brew tea.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can you bring the brazier over?” she asked Erfan. She could ask Rahan or the weirdo tactician, but it would be a fail as they were so weak they would knock it over, so she didn’t feel inclined to ask for their help.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Certainly.” Erfan brought the brazier over with ease.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao picked up the fire tongs, and placed the amethyst skull onto the charcoal. The crystal rolled.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Oh?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The ash-covered skull quickly changed colour. The beautiful wisteria-like purple lightened, turning whitish, then was tinged with a yellowish hue.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Done.” Maomao picked up the skull with the fire tongs. She blew on it. The ash dispersed and a deep yellow skull came into view.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“The colour changed?” The grandson’s eyes were rounded in shock.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“LIke how metals melt in high temperatures, gemstones also change colour. Amethyst easily changes colours, and if under constant sunlight, it would fade to a bluish shade,” Maomao explained.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And when put under high temperatures like a fire, the gemstone would crack and change colours.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Have you shown the dragon statuette to outsiders?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“No, we rarely show it. We would show it to our guests during formal announcements like a transfer of headship, but there was fire before that happened,” the matriarch said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Then, no one could have known of it, right? That a clan that wasn’t of the imperial family possessing a statuette of a four-clawed dragon, and such. And not to mention, if it were to be grasping an orb of deep yellow that resembled ochre…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“H-how can there be such a coincidence?” The grandson’s face was ghastly pale. “Th-then, if the heirloom was only partially burnt in the fire, wouldn’t that mean my clan would have already been punished by the Empress Regnant?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Quite so&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought. However, the fact that it didn’t happen would mean that someone had taken off with the heirloom.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao looked at the matriarch. “Who had taken away the heirloom? …It seems the matriarch has a rough idea about that.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes,” the matriarch said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“More importantly, someone had told you about it, right? About the purpose of the U clan’s visit.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Nothing gets past you, I see. You’re right.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao paused for a bit. “And did the matriarch, having heard the notice, set the treasury on fire?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The matriarch gave a big nod in reply.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;T/N: In hindsight, how did Papa Rakan even commission that hairstick? Not just dragons and skulls, but &lt;em&gt;purple &lt;/em&gt;skulls. &lt;s&gt;Is this his way of showing his support to Maomao joining the imperial family? &lt;/s&gt;But skulls though&amp;#8230;.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-small-font-size"&gt;Ochre, 黄丹 (oudan or ouni), is actually a shade of orange, but the novel wanted to keep a yellow theme, so hence yellow red. It is also the colour reserved for the crown prince in the Japanese imperial family.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-18-rabbit-and-dragon/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-17-the-shins-heirloom-2/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-4231-670843c5d9c6b' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20241010#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=4231&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-4231-670843c5d9c6b' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-4231-670843c5d9c6b' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/12-17-the-shins-heirloom-2/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
